give @s written_book{pages:['["",{"text":"Villager Curing","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:table_of_contents"}},{"text":"\\n\\nIf you find a Zombie Villager then you can cure them into a regular villager. You just need a regular golden apple and a Weakness Potion (","color":"reset"},{"text":"See Potion Guide","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:potion"}},{"text":").","color":"reset"}]','{"text":"If you don\\u2019t want to go to the Nether for the Weakness Potion, you can also use a Witch who will occasionally throw them when trying to attack you."}','{"text":"Step one is to get your Zombie Villager. They can be somewhat uncommon so it would be a good idea to save it. Unfortunately they can despawn and you need an anvil in addition to your nametag to keep them around. You can instead give them an item to hold. (Cont.)"}','{"text":"When they pick up an item, they aren\\u2019t allowed to despawn. Simply drop something on the ground near them, it can be a sword, sticks, armor, or a cobblestone block and they should pick it up."}','["",{"text":"Give your Villager the Weakness effect and feed it your golden apple. After a bit of vibrating it will become a normal jobless Villager!\\nOnce you get two Villagers you can breed them together ("},{"text":"See Establishing a Village","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:make_village"}},{"text":").","color":"reset"}]','{"text":"Once a Villager has a job (and has traded at least once) you can get discounts from them. If you let a zombie kill your villager, then it can turn into a zombie villager (0% in Easy, 50% in Normal, 100% in Hard). (Cont.)"}','{"text":"If you then cure that zombie villager then you will get a discount on their offered items! You can repeat this until the price goes down to the minimum (1 item requested). (Cont.)"}','{"text":"Unfortunately the majority of this discount is temporary and other players will not get the discount (only for the player who fed the golden apple), but it can still be worthwhile in some instances."}'],title:"Technical Skyblock Guidebook",author:"Procymbopteryx and Kitty_McTophat",display:{Lore:['{"text":"Villager Curing"}']}}
